<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5028189>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2A–D. Patrera procera (Keyserling, 1891). Male (MCN 10965): A left palp, ventral view; B same, retrolateral view. Female (MCN 3172): C epigynum, ventral view (arrow indicating the excavation at the lateral borders); D same, dorsal view. Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; dTA, dorsal tibial apophysis; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; H, hood; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A–D 0.25mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5028189/files/figure.png" .

